HEADWORD: Woodsy
<hw>Woods"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to
the woods or forest.</def> <mark>[Colloq. U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It [sugar making] is <qex>woodsy</qex>, and savors of trees.</q>
<rj><qau>J. Burroughs.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

